Is it wise to sell a hdb and a condo which are in both husband and wife name ....then husband and wife each get a property under his/her name. In that case  can move to another property and rent out another property without incurring absd. Thanks.
im confused. currently hubby and wife has 1 hdb and 1 condo? so two properties in total?then u want to sell both  and each get 1 property each... so becoming two properties in total?
Provided your quantum for one of property is not high.
One rental can cover the one for purchased
If the price of the property they currently own already stagnate  to sell off and buy another 2 under individual name so ur money can work harder for you why not?

And do it while you can still get loan  before you know it  when you decide to restructure your portfolio yrs later you may not be eligible for the amt needed. And doing it now when the rates are good
Yes. Currently total 2 properties held by wife and husband.
iif u are changing to 2 bigger  bettter properties  so be it.if not  1 rental income  1 current home is good

In my opinion it really depends on your financial health. If financial means allows  it will be ideal to get 2 properties  a rental home generates income to pay for it’s own mortgage is a plus. Real estate hedges well against inflation and has a sustainable capital growth. 😉
